No correlation between features so predictive modelling is not possible. We can only generate inference about the population using given sample dataset. We will be using Different Hypothesis testing method to test some hypothesis about the population.

One Sample T-Test: 1.) H0: Average sleep quality is 7. Ha: Average sleep quality is not equal to 7 2.) H0: Average productivity score is 7 Ha: Average productivity score is not equal to 7

Two Sample T-Test: 1.) H0: There is no difference in average sleep quality of males and females. Ha: There is difference in average sleep quality of males and females. 2.) H0: There is no difference in average work hours between individuals with low stress and those with high stress. Ha: There is difference in average work hours between individuals with low stress and those with high stress.

ANOVA: 1.) H0: Productivity Score is same across different age group Ha: Productivity Score is different across different age group 2.) H0: Productivity Score is same across different stress levels Ha: Productivity Score is different across different stress levels

One Sample T-Test: H0: Average sleep quality is 7. Ha: Average sleep quality is not equal to 7

t_test_sleep_quality <- t.test(df$`Sleep Quality`, mu = 7)
print("Sleep Quality T Test")

print(t_test_sleep_quality)
